Me & my husband brought my nephew here because he loves instant ramen & we wanted him to try something new. After being recommended to this place I made sure to look at reviews first & we was instantly excited to come. Our food was great & we was having an amazing time just enjoying each other company until it was time to pay. I already knew they didn’t accept cards but I also knew they had an ATM in the restaurant ((previous reviews)) my husband went to the ATM and withdrew cash and immediately paid. One of the ladies came back with only one of the 20s and tells us they do not accept “old bills” And that my husband had to either get a new 20 out the ATM or change it at a store.... now I understand how one can think about counterfeit money but the restaurant is not big you can literally see the entire thing from your seat. The waitress saw my husband go to the ATM in their restaurant & immediately hand her the cash that came out. We had to send my nephew to a store to Change the 20 because they refused to take “old bills” what ever that means. I will never be coming back to this restaurant & it’s sad because I actually enjoyed the food.

This place has good food but they don’t accept cash and they don’t accept old money what ever that means I had to go three different stores just to change an (old twenty) dollar bill that I’ve withdrawn from their atm because they don’t accept old money never have I be more insulted in my life never coming here again anywhere else I go they accept money of any kind

This is a neighborhood gem! Ben had the Tan Tan, which had a broth that was mildly coconut, sesame, chili, and garlic. My Shoyu with chicken dumpling was super, with flavorful broth, perfectly al dente noodles, and chicken and chive meatballs. We tried the Ononmiyai pancake which has something interestingly smokey and fishy along with chives and nori. I would have preferred it without the mayonnaise drizzle.

The black tonkotsu is rich and has a good depth of flavor without being greasy. The ramen is on the thicker side which I personally prefer and pairs well with the broth. The broth has a very well rounded umami flavor, and nicely cooked chashu making it a delightful bowl of ramen. This place is cash only. Also has a good selection of Japanese beer and sake.
